1
00:00:11,700 --> 00:00:13,100
I'll tell my mom on you.

2
00:00:13,167 --> 00:00:15,400
We will file a child abuse case
against you!

3
00:00:15,467 --> 00:00:17,700
What if Mookie files
a kidnapping case against you?

4
00:00:17,767 --> 00:00:19,433
She can also file
a bullying case against you.

5
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:21,500
Ma'am Olive is already
out of the hospital.

6
00:00:21,567 --> 00:00:22,267
What?

7
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,633
Flor, why is the door open?

8
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:24,267
Flor!

9
00:00:24,333 --> 00:00:25,467
Madam!

10
00:00:25,533 --> 00:00:27,667
Are you going to follow me
even in my own house?

11
00:00:27,733 --> 00:00:29,533
I might not see you again.

12
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:30,633
I'll miss you.

13
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:32,833
Mother, they don't have
the same attitude.

14
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,500
I won't take care of her
in the hospital

15
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:36,100
if I'm not comfortable with her.

16
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:38,433
Just because you feel okay

17
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:40,300
doesn't mean you're already
doing well.

18
00:00:41,433 --> 00:00:43,900
Mookie's real mother is back.

19
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:46,233
You're done being
a mother for a day.

20
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:47,533
Whose is this?

21
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:50,933
Did Emma take care of you
while I was in the hospital?

22
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:53,933
Of course not, Mommy.

23
00:00:54,367 --> 00:00:55,600
Tell me the truth.

24
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,300
Mommy, she really didn't.

25
00:01:33,567 --> 00:01:34,267
Promise.

26
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,100
Emma?

27
00:02:18,167 --> 00:02:19,633
Can you come back tomorrow?

28
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:22,067
The curtains need to be washed.

29
00:02:22,533 --> 00:02:23,633
Sure.

30
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:26,400
I'd love that.
So I can also see Mookie.

31
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:27,933
Perfect.

32
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,633
Ma'am Olive has a scheduled
checkup tomorrow.

33
00:02:29,700 --> 00:02:31,467
She won't be here.

34
00:02:31,533 --> 00:02:32,300
Really?

35
00:02:39,267 --> 00:02:39,933
Ma'am.

36
00:02:44,633 --> 00:02:46,267
Whose coin purse is this?

37
00:02:57,567 --> 00:02:59,000
It's mine, Ma'am.

38
00:03:00,033 --> 00:03:00,833
Yours?

39
00:03:01,900 --> 00:03:04,500
So you went into Mookie's room.

40
00:03:05,967 --> 00:03:07,067
No, Ma'am.

41
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:12,867
Why is this in Mookie's room
if it's yours?

42
00:03:14,133 --> 00:03:15,700
That's my coin purse.

43
00:03:15,767 --> 00:03:17,967
But Flor asked
if she could have it.

44
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,533
Why aren't you taking care
of what I gave you?

45
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,267
You leave it everywhere.

46
00:03:22,367 --> 00:03:23,500
Yes, Ma'am.

47
00:03:23,567 --> 00:03:24,800
I asked Emma for that.

48
00:03:24,867 --> 00:03:30,867
But I didn't notice I dropped
it. My pockets are shallow.

49
00:03:31,700 --> 00:03:32,567
I'm sorry.

50
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:36,233
Where were you when I was
in the hospital?

51
00:03:37,233 --> 00:03:37,833
Ma'am?
I was at home.

52
00:03:39,767 --> 00:03:44,133
I took care of my husband
because he was sick.

53
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:45,433
Are you sure?

54
00:03:46,033 --> 00:03:49,333
Yes. You can ask my mother
about it.

55
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,800
She was with you
at the hospital, right?

56
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:55,467
Weren't you taking care
of my daughter?

57
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:58,200
Why would I do that?

58
00:03:58,267 --> 00:03:59,400
I'm a laundress.

59
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:01,533
Why would I look after Mookie?

60
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:04,067
I'll do it if you'll give me
an extra pay.

61
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:07,267
You really take after your mom.

62
00:04:08,133 --> 00:04:10,433
I'm just being practical, Ma'am.

63
00:04:11,167 --> 00:04:13,567
Nothing is free these days.

64
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,367
You disgust me.

65
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:42,333
Dan, looks like Ma'am Olive
is starting to get suspicious.

66
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:46,867
If that's the case, maybe
you should avoid Mookie.

67
00:04:48,067 --> 00:04:51,433
I can't bear to do it.

68
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,967
Especially earlier,
she was so dejected.

69
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,800
I feel like...

70
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:58,933
she's not taking
the right medicines.

71
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,767
Because she doesn't have
a doctor.

72
00:05:01,867 --> 00:05:03,967
Why would Madam Olive hire
another doctor

73
00:05:04,033 --> 00:05:05,567
when she is a doctor?

74
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,733
Will you use your common sense,
Dear?

75
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:13,767
Didn't you say that Ma'am Olive
isn't a certified doctor?

76
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:15,333
It's just a rumor, Emma.

77
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,967
Just a gossip.

78
00:05:17,033 --> 00:05:19,933
Whatever Ma'am Olive wants
to do with her daughter

79
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:21,233
is none of your business.

80
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:24,033
Madam knows what's
best for her child.

81
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:28,367
No mother would intentionally
torture her child.

82
00:05:37,033 --> 00:05:39,700
I can walk without crutches now,
Dr. Taplac.

83
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:40,900
Good.

84
00:05:40,967 --> 00:05:42,867
But take it easy, Miss Caparas.

85
00:05:42,933 --> 00:05:44,600
If there's any discomfort
or pain...

86
00:05:44,667 --> 00:05:45,900
I'm fine, Doc.

87
00:05:45,967 --> 00:05:46,733
Thank you.

88
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,967
People think I'm harsh, Mookie.

89
00:06:14,033 --> 00:06:16,800
I just don't want us
to be apart.

90
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:34,133
Mother.

91
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:39,267
Mother!

92
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:40,733
Mother!

93
00:06:57,733 --> 00:06:59,667
Who are you calling mother?

94
00:07:03,267 --> 00:07:03,867
It's...

95
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,033
Mommy...

96
00:07:10,267 --> 00:07:11,633
Mommy Lily.

97
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:15,800
The character in the
storybook I am reading.

98
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:23,067
I dreamt of Mommy Lily,
and I was Rosie.

99
00:07:23,133 --> 00:07:25,000
And we got separated.

100
00:07:27,433 --> 00:07:29,267
Such a stupid story.

101
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:33,067
Go back to sleep.

102
00:07:56,233 --> 00:07:59,467
Obet, tell Astrid to hire
a temporary driver

103
00:07:59,533 --> 00:08:02,167
for the pharmacy while
you're driving for me.

104
00:08:02,233 --> 00:08:04,133
Flor, look after Mookie.

105
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:05,067
Yes, Ma'am.

106
00:08:06,433 --> 00:08:07,133
Bye.

107
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,600
What did I tell you
to do when you're sad?

108
00:08:45,533 --> 00:08:46,533
Mother.

109
00:08:46,767 --> 00:08:50,967
Didn't I tell you to close
your eyes and...

110
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:55,967
And think of happy things.

111
00:09:07,267 --> 00:09:08,300
You know what?

112
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:11,867
I've been wanting to hug you
since yesterday.

113
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,933
Me, too.

114
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:20,967
But I'm worried about my leg
right now.

115
00:09:22,867 --> 00:09:25,400
I can't feel it again.

116
00:09:26,667 --> 00:09:28,367
I think it's because
of the medicine

117
00:09:28,467 --> 00:09:30,467
that my mom injected into me.

118
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:32,233
What?

119
00:09:33,967 --> 00:09:38,667
Mookie, I don't want to think
ill of your mom.

120
00:09:39,467 --> 00:09:43,867
But isn't she purposely
making you sick?

121
00:09:43,933 --> 00:09:48,033
You know, Mother, that's what
I think, too.

122
00:09:48,967 --> 00:09:52,267
I was feeling well when we
were in the arcade, right?

123
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:55,900
Nothing bad happened to me
when we went to the arcade.

124
00:09:55,967 --> 00:10:00,367
And we found out I wasn't
allergic to pistachios.

125
00:10:02,667 --> 00:10:05,600
Maybe we need to talk
to your Aunt Astrid.

126
00:10:06,367 --> 00:10:08,433
That's also my plan.

127
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:09,600
She might have an idea

128
00:10:09,667 --> 00:10:13,933
what medicines and injectables
my mom is giving me.

129
00:10:15,533 --> 00:10:17,567
Dear, don't worry.

130
00:10:18,267 --> 00:10:21,600
I'll talk to your Aunt Astrid
when she gets back from Cebu.

131
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:31,567
So?
What are we going to do?

132
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,967
Let's not waste time.

133
00:10:35,933 --> 00:10:37,100
Look at this, Mother.

134
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:41,300
Mom forgot to take it back.

135
00:10:41,967 --> 00:10:44,633
But I found something
on the internet.

136
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:50,400
Rosie and Lily's story
already has a part two.

137
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:54,267
And it's an audiobook.

138
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:56,700
So, we can just listen to it.

139
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:57,967
Okay, okay.

140
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:10,933
If Lily and Rosie think
they can live a quiet life,

141
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:12,667
they are mistaken.

142
00:11:13,733 --> 00:11:17,733
One peaceful night,
they are getting ready to sleep.

143
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,233
I have a surprise for you.

144
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:22,033
But I'll tell you tomorrow.

145
00:11:22,900 --> 00:11:24,300
Come on, Mother.

146
00:11:24,367 --> 00:11:26,233
I might think about it
all night.

147
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:29,200
Go on. Go to sleep.

148
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:36,900
Do you think
I will give up easily?

149
00:11:36,967 --> 00:11:40,800
I won't stop until I get Rosie.

150
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:44,267
Leave us alone!

151
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:44,867
Dear!
You're mine!

152
00:11:46,167 --> 00:11:47,000
Let go of me!

153
00:11:47,067 --> 00:11:48,900
- She's mine!
- Let go of my daughter!

154
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:55,033
Mother, I want to stop listening
to this audiobook.

155
00:11:55,933 --> 00:12:02,033
Iris might succeed in
getting Rosie from Lily.

156
00:12:03,333 --> 00:12:05,200
Dear, that won't happen.

157
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,333
Lily's there.

158
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:10,667
She won't let it happen.

159
00:12:10,733 --> 00:12:14,133
She'll never get separated
from Rosie.

160
00:12:25,267 --> 00:12:25,900
Emma?

161
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:27,800
Mookie?

162
00:12:27,867 --> 00:12:28,967
Mommy.

163
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:42,467
I knew it!

164
00:12:43,467 --> 00:12:44,933
You're talking to each other!

165
00:12:46,033 --> 00:12:47,700
You're both lying to me!

166
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:50,700
Ma'am, please hear me out.

167
00:12:51,567 --> 00:12:54,400
I thought you were leaving,
Mommy.

168
00:12:54,467 --> 00:12:55,600
Is that what you're waiting for?

169
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,200
For me to leave?

170
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,667
So you can talk to this woman?

171
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:01,833
You're ganging up on me!

172
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,033
How long have you
been doing this?

173
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:04,900
How long have you been
doing this behind my back?

174
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,033
Obet.

175
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,800
Let's go back.

176
00:13:28,867 --> 00:13:29,867
Who's that?

177
00:13:30,433 --> 00:13:34,667
I saw you in Mookie's room
when I was in the hospital.

178
00:13:34,733 --> 00:13:35,667
Is that right, Emma?

179
00:13:35,733 --> 00:13:36,967
Mommy.

180
00:13:37,033 --> 00:13:38,467
Mommy, I'm sorry.

181
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:40,200
Damn you both!

182
00:13:40,933 --> 00:13:42,867
- You're making me look like...
- Ma'am!

183
00:13:42,933 --> 00:13:44,067
Ma'am! Please stop!

184
00:13:44,133 --> 00:13:45,233
- You, too!
- Don't hurt her!

185
00:13:45,300 --> 00:13:46,367
You traitor!

186
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,200
Mommy!

187
00:13:48,267 --> 00:13:50,200
Mommy, please!
Emma didn't do anything wrong.

188
00:13:50,267 --> 00:13:51,133
Promise.

189
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:54,967
I'm your mother,
and you dared lie to me.

190
00:13:55,067 --> 00:13:57,233
- So I'll teach you a lesson!
- Ma'am, please don't!

191
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:58,333
- Don't!
- You'll get what you deserve!

192
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:00,033
- Don't hurt, Mookie.
- You, too!

193
00:14:00,733 --> 00:14:03,933
I know what women like you do.

194
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,700
So you can never fool me again.

195
00:14:05,767 --> 00:14:06,600
Come here!
Come here.

196
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:08,267
Ma'am.

197
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:09,467
Mommy!

198
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:10,300
Mommy, please!

199
00:14:10,367 --> 00:14:12,700
Emma didn't do anything wrong!

200
00:14:12,767 --> 00:14:14,033
Mommy!

201
00:14:14,100 --> 00:14:15,100
Mommy!

202
00:14:16,333 --> 00:14:19,000
The nerve of you to disobey me!

203
00:14:23,567 --> 00:14:24,033
Ma'am!
What's going on?

204
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:25,367
Ma'am! Oh, no!
Get up!

205
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:26,867
You're part of it, too!
Ma'am, why?

206
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,867
I trusted you to look
after Mookie.

207
00:14:29,933 --> 00:14:33,967
Turns out, you're letting
a snake in my house!

208
00:14:34,033 --> 00:14:34,867
Ma'am! A snake?

209
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:36,633
Where's the snake?

210
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:37,600
Where is it?

211
00:14:37,667 --> 00:14:40,333
Where did you learn
to become a maid?

212
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,333
- What?
- Did you enroll

213
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:42,400
in a playing dumb
school of acting?

214
00:14:43,133 --> 00:14:44,233
- Ma'am...
- Why did you let

215
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:46,933
this woman go to Mookie's room?

216
00:14:47,667 --> 00:14:52,600
Ma'am, I didn't know
she was in Mookie's room.

217
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,367
So, is this Mookie's fault?

218
00:14:54,967 --> 00:14:55,333
Ma'am!
No, Ma'am.

219
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,700
Mookie didn't do anything wrong.

220
00:14:58,767 --> 00:14:59,733
Liar!

221
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:03,067
I went to her room on my own.

222
00:15:03,167 --> 00:15:06,600
That's not an excuse
to disobey me!

223
00:15:06,667 --> 00:15:08,233
She's always alone.

224
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:11,167
I just want her to have
someone she can talk to.

225
00:15:11,233 --> 00:15:13,533
Are you teaching me
how to be a mother?

226
00:15:14,633 --> 00:15:16,533
I know what's best
for my daughter!

227
00:15:16,967 --> 00:15:18,133
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

228
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:20,067
Please forgive me.

229
00:15:20,133 --> 00:15:24,567
You put Mookie in trouble
because of what you did!

230
00:15:24,633 --> 00:15:27,633
I'll teach her a lesson!

231
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:29,167
Ma'am, please don't hurt her.

232
00:15:29,233 --> 00:15:30,267
Don't hurt Mookie.

233
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:32,767
Take your anger out on me.

234
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:34,067
Hurt me instead, Ma'am!

235
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:40,700
You know, you will never see
how I will discipline Mookie.

236
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:43,400
What do you mean, Ma'am?

237
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:46,800
Say goodbye to your job
as a laundress.

238
00:15:47,667 --> 00:15:48,833
You're jobless now.

239
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:51,433
Because you're fired!

240
00:15:51,833 --> 00:15:52,367
Ma'am.
Get lost!

241
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:54,100
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

242
00:15:54,167 --> 00:15:55,600
Ma'am, please stop.

243
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,667
- Get lost!
- Ma'am! Please have mercy!

244
00:15:59,733 --> 00:16:01,267
Please have mercy!

245
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:09,900
Ma'am.

246
00:16:09,967 --> 00:16:10,367
Ma'am.

247
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:15,800
- Ma'am.
- I warned you a lot of times.

248
00:16:15,867 --> 00:16:17,967
But you didn't listen.

249
00:16:18,033 --> 00:16:19,067
I won't do it again, Ma'am.

250
00:16:19,133 --> 00:16:21,167
Please don't fire me.

251
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:22,600
You won't do it again?

252
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:24,900
I've heard that before.

253
00:16:25,367 --> 00:16:27,533
I won't get near Mookie again.

254
00:16:28,567 --> 00:16:29,867
I didn't become a doctor

255
00:16:29,933 --> 00:16:33,100
to just get fooled by a trash
like you.

256
00:16:33,633 --> 00:16:35,033
Pretty Madam.

257
00:16:35,100 --> 00:16:36,333
What did my daughter do?

258
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:38,067
Why are you firing her?

259
00:16:38,133 --> 00:16:41,167
Why don't you ask
your darn daughter?

260
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:43,300
Maybe we can talk
things over, Madam.

261
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:45,200
You're just the same.

262
00:16:45,967 --> 00:16:49,033
Traitors, if not greedy
for money.

263
00:16:49,100 --> 00:16:51,700
Get out of here and never
come back.

264
00:16:58,367 --> 00:17:00,433
- Gosh, Emma.
- What did you do?

265
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:03,233
Madam Olive transformed
into a monster.

266
00:17:03,300 --> 00:17:06,100
Why did you get
near her daughter?

267
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:08,467
Please.

268
00:17:08,867 --> 00:17:09,733
We're going to talk first.

269
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,967
- But...
- Step back.

270
00:17:11,033 --> 00:17:11,767
Tell us everything later.
Step back.

271
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:15,633
Tell us all the details later.

272
00:17:22,867 --> 00:17:23,800
Mommy, please.

273
00:17:24,533 --> 00:17:25,867
Don't fire Emma.

274
00:17:25,933 --> 00:17:28,400
She didn't do anything wrong.

275
00:17:28,467 --> 00:17:30,867
You're defending that trash?

276
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:33,800
Emma is a good person.

277
00:17:33,867 --> 00:17:35,533
And you believed her?

278
00:17:36,633 --> 00:17:38,900
You don't know Emma's family!

279
00:17:39,733 --> 00:17:41,467
Her mother is greedy for money.

280
00:17:42,067 --> 00:17:45,333
She's pretending to be kind
because they need money!

281
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,667
That's not true.

282
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:50,033
What happened?

283
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:52,767
Mother.

284
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:55,800
I'm worried about Mookie.
Ma'am Olive might hurt her.

285
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:59,133
You're thinking about Mookie?

286
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:00,833
Think about your job.

287
00:18:00,900 --> 00:18:03,967
You lost it because
you're so stubborn.

288
00:18:05,233 --> 00:18:05,933
Mommy!

289
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:08,033
Don't you believe me?

290
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:09,333
Don't you want to believe me?

291
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:11,833
You don't know anything
about the outside world.

292
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:13,567
That's why you're gullible!

293
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:15,200
No, Mommy.

294
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:19,000
Emma isn't that kind of person.

295
00:18:19,967 --> 00:18:23,300
And if she's fooling me,
I will let her!

296
00:18:24,100 --> 00:18:25,833
I don't care, Mommy.

297
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:27,933
Because I'm happy
when I'm with her.

298
00:18:33,033 --> 00:18:34,467
What did you say?

299
00:18:37,367 --> 00:18:41,433
You're happy
when you're with Emma?

300
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:45,333
She's the only person
who makes me feel things

301
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:48,767
that I don't feel from you.

302
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:49,600
Stop it!

303
00:18:50,733 --> 00:18:51,833
Stop it!

304
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:56,667
I'm happy whenever she reads me
a storybook.

305
00:18:56,767 --> 00:18:57,967
I forget everything.

306
00:18:58,033 --> 00:19:02,367
Because even if it's just
a simple thing, I feel loved.

307
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:05,167
Something that I don't feel
from you.

308
00:19:05,233 --> 00:19:06,567
What did you say?

309
00:19:06,633 --> 00:19:09,633
I only want to make her
daughter happy, Mother.

310
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:11,367
Make Mookie happy?

311
00:19:11,433 --> 00:19:13,100
You should make
Madam happy instead.

312
00:19:13,167 --> 00:19:14,767
She's the one paying you.

313
00:19:15,733 --> 00:19:18,533
So she's right all along that
you're greedy for money.

314
00:19:19,067 --> 00:19:20,133
How dare you.

315
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:22,700
You call it practicality.

316
00:19:22,767 --> 00:19:24,367
It's for your own interest.

317
00:19:24,433 --> 00:19:26,833
You don't consider
Mookie's feelings.

318
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:28,833
That's not true, Emma.

319
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:31,033
I'm not surprised.

320
00:19:31,100 --> 00:19:32,533
When I gave birth to Kayla,

321
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:34,700
didn't you want me
to give her up for adoption?

322
00:19:34,767 --> 00:19:37,100
Son of a gun, Emma.

323
00:19:37,167 --> 00:19:38,867
Do we have to bring up the past?

324
00:19:44,567 --> 00:19:45,600
Is this it?

325
00:19:46,133 --> 00:19:47,267
- Is this it?
- Mommy.

326
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:47,900
No!
Mommy, give it to me!

327
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:50,133
- Mommy!
- Let go of it!

328
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:51,433
Give it to me, Mommy!

329
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,400
- Please!
- Is this it?

330
00:19:53,467 --> 00:19:54,767
Mommy!

331
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:55,833
Is this it?

332
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:57,567
Is this the reason?

333
00:19:57,633 --> 00:19:58,633
Is this it?

334
00:19:58,700 --> 00:19:59,733
- Is this it?
- No!

335
00:20:00,333 --> 00:20:01,033
This?

336
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:02,100
This?

337
00:20:02,167 --> 00:20:03,967
- This?
- No!

338
00:20:04,033 --> 00:20:05,600
- This?
- No!

339
00:20:07,667 --> 00:20:08,467
- No!
- This?

340
00:20:08,533 --> 00:20:09,533
This!

341
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:11,933
This!

342
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,267
Mommy, no!

343
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:17,333
Mommy! Everything!

344
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:20,300
You're forbidding me everything!

345
00:20:20,367 --> 00:20:21,800
Everything!

346
00:20:21,867 --> 00:20:25,133
I do everything you want,
don't I?

347
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,433
Why, Mommy?

348
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:28,267
Are you now talking back?

349
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:30,267
When did you learn
to talk back?

350
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,600
Mommy, why don't you want me
to be happy?

351
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,400
Is this it?
There!

352
00:20:36,233 --> 00:20:37,300
Eat it!

353
00:20:37,367 --> 00:20:38,867
Eat it! Do you want this?

354
00:20:38,933 --> 00:20:40,067
Eat it!

355
00:20:40,133 --> 00:20:43,800
You learned to talk back to me
because of that Emma!

356
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:45,667
You're ungrateful!

357
00:20:45,733 --> 00:20:47,000
I raised you!

358
00:20:47,067 --> 00:20:48,800
I did everything for you!

359
00:20:48,867 --> 00:20:50,633
And now, you're talking back
to me?

360
00:20:53,267 --> 00:20:54,733
Ungrateful!

361
00:21:12,733 --> 00:21:15,933
You don't know how I feel.

362
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,800
Because you've never
lost a child.

363
00:21:17,867 --> 00:21:18,633
Really?

364
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:20,100
Why?

365
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:22,967
Do you know everything
I went through?

366
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:27,400
Were you there when I thought
it was the end of the world?

367
00:21:29,067 --> 00:21:33,067
Emma, I know how you felt
when you lost Baby Kayla.

368
00:21:33,133 --> 00:21:35,433
And I also know how you
feel right now

369
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:36,967
because of Mookie!

370
00:21:37,033 --> 00:21:38,033
Of course, I know!

371
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:39,833
I lost a child, too!

372
00:21:46,633 --> 00:21:47,933
What did you say?

373
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:48,600
Let's talk later.
Mother.

374
00:21:49,667 --> 00:21:50,667
- Mother, what did you say?
- Let me go.

375
00:21:50,733 --> 00:21:51,600
You lost a child?
- What are you doing?
- Mother!

376
00:21:52,633 --> 00:21:53,167
Yes!

377
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,267
I felt like I lost a child.

378
00:21:57,800 --> 00:22:00,200
Because you were
seriously ill.

379
00:22:00,267 --> 00:22:01,500
I was looking for money.

380
00:22:01,567 --> 00:22:04,033
I left you in the care
of someone I know.

381
00:22:04,867 --> 00:22:06,433
When I went back,
you were no longer there.

382
00:22:08,567 --> 00:22:09,667
I looked for you.

383
00:22:09,733 --> 00:22:10,867
I almost went crazy.

384
00:22:10,933 --> 00:22:12,733
I couldn't find you.

385
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,433
I thought I had lost you.

386
00:22:16,900 --> 00:22:18,600
But I got you back.

387
00:22:18,667 --> 00:22:19,400
Mother.

388
00:22:20,067 --> 00:22:21,900
So don't accuse me...

389
00:22:21,967 --> 00:22:27,267
Don't say that
I don't care.

390
00:22:27,333 --> 00:22:30,467
Because you don't know
what I went through.

391
00:22:30,533 --> 00:22:32,100
You weren't there. You weren't.

392
00:22:33,567 --> 00:22:36,433
Mother, sorry for what I said.

393
00:22:37,067 --> 00:22:39,867
I just don't want to get
separated from Mookie.

394
00:22:40,467 --> 00:22:41,233
Whatever.

395
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:43,667
You always think I don't care.

396
00:22:43,733 --> 00:22:46,300
You always say
I have no concern.

397
00:22:47,167 --> 00:22:49,033
She's not in any way related
to you.

398
00:22:49,133 --> 00:22:50,000
She's not your daughter.

399
00:22:50,067 --> 00:22:51,567
But you care for her.
What about me?

400
00:22:51,633 --> 00:22:53,433
You're my daughter.
I'm your mother.

401
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:57,667
I hope you understand that
I just don't want you hurt.

402
00:22:57,733 --> 00:22:59,067
I don't want you
to get harmed.

403
00:22:59,667 --> 00:23:03,933
Something terrible might happen
to you because of that Mookie.

404
00:23:08,967 --> 00:23:09,867
What did you talk about?
What happened?

405
00:23:10,767 --> 00:23:11,067
Tell us.

406
00:23:11,133 --> 00:23:12,167
Quit it.

407
00:23:12,233 --> 00:23:14,533
Come on...

408
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:16,400
We're just worried for you.

409
00:23:16,467 --> 00:23:19,000
Tell us what happened.

410
00:23:19,067 --> 00:23:19,967
Mother, come on.

411
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:21,067
I'll bring you home.

412
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:22,333
- No need.
- Let's go, Mother.

413
00:23:22,833 --> 00:23:23,667
He wants us to get in the car.

414
00:23:23,733 --> 00:23:25,333
This is air-conditioned.

415
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:26,167
Mother!

416
00:23:26,233 --> 00:23:27,400
We'll go with her.

417
00:23:27,467 --> 00:23:28,033
Okay.

418
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:29,200
Be safe. Bye!

419
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,400
Ligaya! BFF!

420
00:23:31,467 --> 00:23:32,200
Hey!

421
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:37,933
Emma.

422
00:23:39,933 --> 00:23:40,733
What happened?

423
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:42,833
Mother seems to be
in a bad mood.

424
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:44,833
I'll explain at home.

425
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:46,733
Let's go.

426
00:24:35,967 --> 00:24:37,633
I'm begging you.

427
00:24:37,700 --> 00:24:40,400
Please forgive Emma.

428
00:24:40,467 --> 00:24:42,867
Please, Madam.

429
00:24:42,933 --> 00:24:44,267
Mommy, please.

430
00:24:44,333 --> 00:24:46,533
Let Emma go back.

431
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:49,000
I feel bad for her family.

432
00:24:49,067 --> 00:24:52,533
I'm glad you let Emma
return to her job.

433
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:55,567
It's not easy to hire
a laundress these days.

434
00:24:55,633 --> 00:24:57,233
Is that the only reason?

435
00:24:57,300 --> 00:24:59,367
Or do you feel sorry for Ligaya?

436
00:25:00,100 --> 00:25:02,267
I'm warning you, Emma.

437
00:25:02,367 --> 00:25:05,167
Stay the hell away
from my daughter.

438
00:25:05,233 --> 00:25:09,333
If you repeat what you did,
I won't just fire you.

439
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:13,867
I will find a way to kick
you out of your house

440
00:25:13,933 --> 00:25:15,433
and out of this place.

441
00:25:19,733 --> 00:25:21,800
Mother is back.
